With morning’s dawn so fresh and fair,
I breathe the fragrance of the air.
The world awakens, bright and new,
And nature sings her praises true.

The sun ascends with golden hue,
The flowers bloom in every view.
In every moment, every glance,
Nature invites me to her dance.


- Julia Ward Howe
